description:
The plagues fell on Egypt with varying severity, but Pharaoh remained unmoved until the 10th plague, the death of all of the firstborns in the land of Egypt. This affected all, except those who observed the first Passover service. When they reached the Red Sea, Moses was instructed to hold out his rod across the sea. Miraculously the waters parted, and the Israelites were free to cross on dry ground. Israel was now free to leave, yet the journey would not be without drama...
